1. Open Gazebo
2. Go to Edit → Model Editor
3. Add Cube → place in environment
4. Link Inspector:
   - Height = 0.4 m (Z pose)
   - Visual/Collision: X = 2 m, Y = 1 m, Z = 0.15 m
5. Add Cylinder
   - Pose → Roll = 1.507
   - Visual/Collision: Radius = 0.3 m, Length = 0.25 m
   - Create Revolute Joint, align with cube
   - Duplicate for opposite wheel
6. Add Sphere
   - Visual/Collision: Radius = 0.2 m
   - Joint Type: Ball
7. Add Depth Camera → from Model Database (http://models.gazebosim...)
8. Define all joints → Create
9. Add Model Plugin:
   - Name: follower
   - Filename: libFollowerPlugin.so
10. Save model as "simplediffbot"
11. Exit Model Editor
12. Run the Simulator
